<h1>About HMCA</h1>
<p></p>Health Management Company of America (HMCA), majority-owned by FONAR Corporation, provides non-medical management 
        services for diagnostic imaging centers. At present, HMCA employs approximately 
        300 full-time employees and manages 26 centers in New York and Florida. 
        The 26 centers are collectively equipped with 34 MRI scanners, most of 
        them with FONAR Stand-Up&reg; MRIs. (The FONAR Stand-Up&reg; MRI is also 
        known as the UPRIGHT&reg; Multi-Position&#8482; MRI). Several Stand-Up&reg; 
        MRI centers also offer complementary diagnostic equipment, such as High-Field 
        1.5T MRIs, 3.0T Whole-Body MRIs, 1.5T Extremity MRIs, and X-ray.</p>

<p>HMCA&acute;s predecessors originated in Melville, Long Island, New York in 1989.  Experienced in every aspect of non-medical office management, 
the Company&acute;s <a href="services.php">Centralized Management Services include</a>: </p>
 
 <ul class="about">
 <li>Facility Staffing</li>
 <li>Radiology Support </li>
 <li>Billing and Collections</li>
 <li>Credentialing and Contracting </li>
 <li>Human Resources</li>
 <li>Marketing</li>
 <li>Compliance</li>
 <li>Purchasing</li>
 <li>Accounting</li>
 <li>Office Management</li>
 <li>Reporting</li>
 <li>Information Technology (IT) Support</li>
 <li>Transcription</li>
 </ul>
 
   
